<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870106-0033 </DOCNO><HL> Carolina Freight NamesJohn L. Fraley Chairman</HL><DD> 01/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CAO WNEWS </IN><DATELINE> CHERRYVILLE, N.C.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Carolina Freight Corp. said John L. Fraley, vice chairman, was named chairman. Mr. Fraley, 66 years old, succeeds C. Grier Beam, 80, the founder of the freight transportation company, who was named chairman emeritus.    Mr. Beam will be succeeded as a director by former U.S. Sen. James T. Broyhill. Howard H. Haworth, former North Carolina secretary of commerce, also was named a director. He succeeds J. Willis Cantey, who died in October. </TEXT></DOC>